    <p>Here is a movie marathon you can­not refuse, so catch this mafia crime se­ries be­fore they ro­tate out of Net­flix.</p>
    <p>Di­rec­tor Fran­cis Ford Cop­pola showed us how to love the mur­der­ous Cor­leone fam­ily.</p>
    <p>Be­sides spawn­ing a hun­dred quotable lines – such as “I’m go­ing to make him an of­fer he can’t refuse” – the se­ries set the tem­plate for HBO’s The So­pra­nos (1999 to 2007) and Suc­ces­sion (2018 to 2019) and dozens of other works about the dirty work that keeps dy­nas­ties hum­ming.</p>
    <p>Watch on Net­flix:</p>
    <p>The God­fa­ther (1972)</p>
    <p>The God­fa­ther Part II (1974) The God­fa­ther Part III (1990)</p>

